I've made the following changes:

1. Added a new parameter to the SignInScreen composable: `onNavigateToMain: () -> Unit = {}` which will handle navigation to the main page
2. Added a prominent sign-up button that matches the app's design aesthetic:
 - Used a teal color (`Color(0xFF02A3AF)`) to match the styling of the "Sign In" link
 - Added rounded corners with a `RoundedCornerShape(28.dp)` for a modern look
 - Sized appropriately with `height(56.dp)` to be easily tappable
 - Positioned below the form fields and above the social login section
3. Added an "Or continue with" text above the social login options to better organize the UI flow
4. Consistently styled the button to match the existing UI elements

The button will call the `onNavigateToMain` function when pressed, which you can implement in your navigation logic to navigate to the main page once it's created."}]}

